<P>SOME LETTERS, Containing An Account of what seemed most Remarkable <HI>in Travelling</HI> through SWITZERLAND, ITALY, Some parts of GERMANY, &amp;c. In the Years 1685. and 1686.</P>
<P>Written by <HI>G. Burnet, D. D.</HI> to the Ho^b^l^e <HI>R. B.</HI></P>
<P>The Third Edition, <HI>Corrected,</HI> and <HI>Altered</HI> in some places by the <HI>Author.</HI></P>
<P>To which is added, an <HI>Appendix,</HI> containing some <HI>Re|marks</HI> on <HI>Switzerland</HI> and <HI>Italy,</HI> writ by a <HI>Person</HI> of <HI>Quality,</HI> and communicated to the <HI>Author.</HI></P>
<P>Together with <HI>a Table</HI> of the <HI>Contents</HI> of each <HI>Letter.</HI></P>
<P>AMSTERDAM Printed for the <HI>Widow Swart,</HI> Bookseller in the Beurs Stege, 1688.</P>
